    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-10-04T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-10-04T06:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <head>91. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d91fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 310.361/10–457. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Moscow</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1957-10-04T14:00:00+03:00">October 4, 1957—2 p.m.</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>688. Department pass <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_DRH1">Davis</persName> called on <persName corresp="#p_KAG1"
                        >Kulazhenkov</persName>, acting chief American section, at noon October 4
                    and read him oral statement facts as outlined paragraphs 1 and 2 of <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 399<note n="2" xml:id="d91fn2">
                        <ref target="#d89">Document 89</ref>.</note> concerning picketing at Soviet
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Mission headquarters.</p>
                <p>In reply <persName corresp="#p_KAG1">Kulazhenkov</persName> asserted
                    demonstrations were “not peaceful”, as Soviet Foreign Ministry had already three
                    times reminded Embassy, and these demonstrations interfered with normal
                    functioning and work of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Mission. <persName
                        corresp="#p_DRH1">Davis</persName> then asked for specific instances of
                    improper or disorderly acts which might be investigated to which <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAG1">Kulazhenkov</persName> replied he could not add anything
                    to what <persName corresp="#p_FNT1">Fedorenko</persName> had said about
                    demonstrations.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DRH1">Davis</persName> then inquired whether Soviet
                    government was insisting that all peaceful picketing be forbidden by US
                    authorities. <persName corresp="#p_KAG1">Kulazhenkov</persName> then stated he
                    considered information concerning measures taken by police authorities as
                    “intention” of US authorities to insure normal conditions for work of Soviet
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Mission and he would so inform his
                    government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TLE1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Thompson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
